2. The Will of God, which is the Foundation and Rule of his Worſhip, is only revealed to us in the Scriptures, whence it is manifeſt, that in Worſhip, all men are bound to keep cloſe to the Word, and beſides the reaſon that is in the thing it ſelf, the Command is expreſs, Exod. 23.13. Deut. 4.2. Gal. 6.10. [
                     〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                  ] according to this Canon, or Rule: This is true Canonical Obedience. So Rom. 12.7. [
                     〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                  ] is properly Word-Service; (i.e.) ſuch as the Word preſcribes.
